edu.uoregon.autograder.model
Class Grader

java.lang.Object
  edu.uoregon.autograder.model.Grader

public class Grader
extends java.lang.Object

Author:
Kurt Mueller This class encapsulates grader functionality for testing one program. A grader executes a sequence of GraderTasks (stored in the tasks field) sequentially, using input parameters from the input field.

doTasks

public void doTasks()
Get the first task, and if it's not disabled, do it. Then get that task's next task and do it. Repeat until all tasks are done.

toHTML

public java.lang.String toHTML()
Of course, this is not a good long-term solution, because you really shouldn't have a lot of HTML hardcoded in your java classes, but it works for now. The http-equiv="refresh" content="5" tag causes the page to automatically refresh every 5 seconds. Would be better to push changes to the web page, but again, this is just a start.

Returns:
a String with a complete HTML page that shows the status of the tasks in the grader's workflow, and of the grader itself.

toConciseHTMLTableRow

public java.lang.String toConciseHTMLTableRow()
Returns:
a String with HTML for a single table row (or two table rows, in the case of completed Robotium tasks), showing the status and results (if complete) of the grader. This is used by the MultigraderServlet, to show the status of all queued, running, and completed graders on a single page. It does not show the status of all of a grader's tasks, like the full-page toHMTL() method above.
